The Executive Secretary, Nigeria Christian Pilgrim Commission, NCPC, Rev Dr. Yakubu Pam, has congratulated President Muhammadu Buhari on the occasion of this year’s Democracy Day. In a statement signed by his Special Assistant on Media and Public Relations, Pam Ayuba, the NCPC boss, as part of his democracy day message, said President Buhari has done a lot to change the face of Nigeria in spite of challenges confronting the country. According to Pam, “Nigeria will rise again. We will overcome our challenges and I see a new Nigeria emerging stronger than ever before. “The storm will soon cease. We shall arrive our destination safely and we shall smile again. “Mr President Sir, be still. The challenges you see today will soon give way. Your end shall be better than the beginning. “Your decision to bring this Democracy Day to June 12 is a clear testament of your envisioned legacy of bequeathing a lasting memory to Nigerians now and beyond!” To my governor, Rt. Hon. Barr. Simon Bako Lalong, I celebrate with you and the entire citizens of the state on this auspicious moment. You have demonstrated by far your commitment and love for your people the past six years on the saddle as Governor.” Pam further encouraged the governor to be strong and courageous, even as he prayed for the continued peace of the country and Plateau State.